Welcome to the PyMongeAmpere wiki!

First of all, you have to download [MongeAmpere](https://github.com/mrgt/MongeAmpere). It's not necessary to compile it but PyMongeAmpere must be located in the same repository.

Once you have installed all the dependencies, as explained [here](InstallingDependencies), building is rather straightforward. Create a out-of-source build folder:

``` sh
cd path/to/PyMongeAmpere/..
mkdir PyMongeAmpere-build
cd PyMongeAmpere-build
```

Configure and build:

``` sh
cmake ../PyMongeAmpere
```

``` sh
make
```

## Dependencies installation

sudo apt-get install cmake-curses-gui
sudo apt-get install libboost-python-dev
sudo apt-get install libeigen3-dev 
sudo apt-get install python-scipy
sudo apt-get install libcgal-dev
sudo apt-get install cimg-dev

sudo apt-get install python-dev
sudo apt-get install libsuitesparse-dev 

sudo apt-get install python-matplotlib


# Pour systèmes plus anciens

N'installez avec linuxbrew que les bibliothèque dont vous avez besoin.
cd ~/.linuxbrew/Library/Formula
gedit python.rb
Rajouter à la variable args l88 --enable-shared pour installer la librairie dynamique

brew install python
brew install numpy
brew install scipy
brew install matplotlib
brew install pillow

brew install eigen
cd ~/.linuxbrew/Library/Formula
gedit boost.rb
Enlever "python" entre les crochets l75.
brew install boost

ccmake ../PyMongeAmpere/ -DEIGEN3_INCLUDE_DIR=/home/ROCQ/mokaplan/slegrand/.linuxbrew/include/eigen3/ -DBoost_INCLUDE_DIR=/home/ROCQ/mokaplan/slegrand/.linuxbrew/Cellar/boost/1.56.0/include/ -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=/home/ROCQ/mokaplan/common/opt/gcc/4.8.1/bin/g++ -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER=/home/ROCQ/mokaplan/common/opt/gcc/4.8.1/bin/gcc


